==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Groundwork
<hw>Ground"work`</hw> <pr>(ground"w⟦ucir⟧rk`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<def>That which forms the foundation or support of anything; the basis;
the essential or fundamental part; first principle; <as>as, development
of a convenient DNA sequencing technique layed the <ex>groundwork</ex>
for many of the subsequent advances in molecular genetics</as>.</def>
<rj><au>Dryden.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

